  </sponsors>
  <source>Meir Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Ambrosia is known for its allergenicity in the USA causing hay fever and asthma. Israel has
      always been considered &quot;clean&quot; of Ambrosia but over the past years growth of Ambrosia plants
      has been detected in several locations in Israel.

      In the proposed study, patients referred for routine allergic evaluation will also be skin
      tested with Ambrosia allergens, in addition to their regular prick skin tests with all other
      airborne allergens.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
